{"nmem_brain_package": "1.0", "manifest": {"id": "a89c33c5-af37-4ef3-9e56-ab3abe490a8b", "name": "git-workflows", "display_name": "Git Workflows", "description": "Essential git knowledge: branching strategies, conventional commits, interactive rebase, conflict resolution, security practices, and debugging with bisect and blame.", "version": "1.0.0", "author": "neural-memory", "license": "CC-BY-4.0", "tags": ["git", "version-control", "workflow", "branching", "code-review"], "category": "devops", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.448031+00:00", "exported_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.448031+00:00", "nmem_version": "4.33.0", "stats": {"neuron_count": 19, "synapse_count": 10, "fiber_count": 0}, "size_bytes": 11834, "size_tier": "micro", "content_hash": "sha256:a5051f01b708090dbad912ccfeab50481e807ded0b458a5a7e7d61382c7b211d", "scan_summary": {"risk_level": "clean", "finding_count": 0, "safe": true}, "rating_avg": 0.0, "rating_count": 0, "download_count": 0}, "snapshot": {"brain_id": "git-workflows", "brain_name": "git-workflows", "config": {}, "exported_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447818+00:00", "fibers": [], "metadata": {"quality": "curated", "source": "seed-generator"}, "neurons": [{"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Chose conventional commits (feat/fix/refactor) over free-form messages because they enable automated changelogs, semantic versioning, and make git log scannable", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447729+00:00", "id": "git-d1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "workflow"], "type": "decision", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447729+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Chose rebase for feature branches over merge because it produces a linear history that's easier to bisect and revert. Only merge for long-lived branches with multiple contributors", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447737+00:00", "id": "git-d2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "branching"], "type": "decision", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447737+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Chose squash-merge for PRs to main because it keeps main history clean (one commit per feature) while preserving detailed commits in the PR for review context", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447739+00:00", "id": "git-d3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "workflow"], "type": "decision", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447739+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "git reflog is the safety net most developers don't know about. It tracks every HEAD movement for 90 days — even after hard reset, you can recover commits with `git reflog` + `git cherry-pick`", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447741+00:00", "id": "git-i1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "recovery"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447741+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Interactive rebase (`git rebase -i`) is the most powerful git tool: reorder, squash, split, edit, or drop commits before pushing. Use it to craft clean commit history from messy development", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447742+00:00", "id": "git-i2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "rebase"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447742+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "git stash is a stack, not a single slot. Use `git stash push -m 'description'` to label stashes, `git stash list` to see them, `git stash pop stash@{2}` to apply a specific one", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447744+00:00", "id": "git-i3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "workflow"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447744+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Atomic commits make bisect, revert, and cherry-pick trivial. Each commit should compile, pass tests, and do ONE thing. If your commit message needs 'and', split it", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447745+00:00", "id": "git-i4", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "best-practices"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447745+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "git blame with -w ignores whitespace, -M detects moved lines, -C detects copied lines from other files. Combined: `git blame -wMC` gives accurate authorship even after refactoring", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447747+00:00", "id": "git-i5", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "debugging"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447747+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Root cause: force-pushing to a shared branch overwrites others' work. Fix: use `--force-with-lease` which fails if the remote has commits you haven't fetched yet", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447748+00:00", "id": "git-e1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "safety"], "type": "error", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447748+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Root cause: committing secrets (.env, API keys) to git means they're in history forever, even after deletion. Fix: use .gitignore from day 1, git-secrets for pre-commit scanning, BFG to rewrite history if leaked", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447750+00:00", "id": "git-e2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "security"], "type": "error", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447750+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Root cause: large merge conflicts from long-lived branches. Prevention: rebase onto main frequently (daily for active branches), keep PRs small (<400 lines), split features into incremental slices", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447752+00:00", "id": "git-e3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "conflicts"], "type": "error", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447752+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Git stores snapshots, not diffs. Each commit points to a tree of blob objects. Identical files across commits share the same blob (content-addressable). Pack files compress old objects for storage efficiency", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447753+00:00", "id": "git-f1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "internals"], "type": "fact", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447753+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Branch naming conventions: feature/ticket-description, fix/ticket-description, release/v1.2.0, hotfix/critical-issue. Slash-separated prefixes enable tab completion and log filtering", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447755+00:00", "id": "git-f2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "conventions"], "type": "fact", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447755+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": ".gitignore patterns: `*.log` ignores all logs, `build/` ignores directory, `!important.log` negates a pattern, `**/temp` matches in any subdirectory. Check with `git check-ignore -v file`", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447756+00:00", "id": "git-f3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "config"], "type": "fact", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447756+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "PR review workflow: 1) Self-review diff first 2) Run CI locally 3) Write description with context and test plan 4) Request review from domain expert 5) Address feedback in fixup commits 6) Squash-merge after approval", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447758+00:00", "id": "git-w1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "code-review"], "type": "workflow", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447758+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Git bisect for bug hunting: 1) `git bisect start` 2) `git bisect bad` (current) 3) `git bisect good v1.0` (known good) 4) Test each checkout 5) Git narrows to the exact breaking commit in O(log n) steps", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447759+00:00", "id": "git-w2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "debugging"], "type": "workflow", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447759+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Release workflow: 1) Create release branch from main 2) Bump version + update changelog 3) Tag with `git tag -a v1.2.0 -m 'Release 1.2.0'` 4) Push tag triggers CI pipeline 5) Merge back to main", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447760+00:00", "id": "git-w3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "release"], "type": "workflow", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447760+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Trunk-based development: everyone commits to main (or short-lived branches). No long-lived feature branches. Feature flags control visibility. This reduces merge conflicts and enables continuous deployment", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447762+00:00", "id": "git-c1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "branching-strategy"], "type": "concept", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447762+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "The three trees of git: Working Directory (your files), Staging Area/Index (next commit preview), HEAD (last commit). `git add` moves to staging, `git commit` moves to HEAD, `git checkout` moves from HEAD to working", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447763+00:00", "id": "git-c2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["git", "mental-model"], "type": "concept", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447763+00:00"}], "synapses": [{"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447779+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "4bf95bdb-8bbe-4764-be58-0e7ac5f28908", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-d1", "target_id": "git-w3", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.8}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447783+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "a19dcbf7-666b-4e62-8dda-4bbd14ac05de", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-d2", "target_id": "git-i2", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.9}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447786+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "ef12a4fc-26a6-4fc1-8dc0-81cdda669638", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-d3", "target_id": "git-i4", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.7}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447788+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "2bd67442-1d69-42e4-8ee9-5fd2799d3939", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-e1", "target_id": "git-d2", "type": "caused_by", "weight": 0.8}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447790+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "b99a5f0f-7c8f-4ad2-926a-630ec963d405", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-e3", "target_id": "git-c1", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.8}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447793+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "586c849b-6b02-493d-80c8-c766cdb5cd1b", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-i1", "target_id": "git-e1", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.7}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447795+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "044d4feb-3016-45f4-ba1f-1f395c090bc5", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-i5", "target_id": "git-w2", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.6}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447800+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "f57f7e1b-7bbb-4147-943f-c81abad68a22", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-f1", "target_id": "git-c2", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.9}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447803+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "fa83ca8e-412d-4f61-abb6-80581cff10ef", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-e2", "target_id": "git-f3", "type": "caused_by", "weight": 0.7}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.447805+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "2f8b2e7b-6a29-4f88-951f-0ba68d21abf7", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "git-w1", "target_id": "git-d3", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.6}], "version": "1"}}